common.Custom filters are different filter opti: Custom filters are different filter options that can be configured. These filters can be enabled by the admin to offer an enhanced search option to the end customers. Based on the filters configured by the admin, the end customers can use them to narrow down their search and find the right product. For example, product variants can be one of the filters, different attributes can also be filters.

common.Title: Title
common.Blogs are articles that are informationa: Blogs are articles that are informational and they are often discussions that are published on the website for the visitors to consume it. A title for the blog article should be appealing and often should help the reader expect the content of the blog article, even before they consume it.
common.The blog article can be mapped to a cate: The blog article can be mapped to a category in order to help the visitors understand the category to which the article belongs to. This will help them expect the content of the blog article, even before they consume it.
common.A blog slug is the part of a blog URL th: A blog slug is the part of a blog URL that identifies a particular page of the blog on a website in an easy-to-read form. In other words, its the part of the blog URL that explains the blog pages content.
common.This is the section, where you can post: This is the section, where you can post the body or the main content of the blog article. You can use the editor for headings and sub-headings, making a content bold or italic, etc.
common.This is the section, where you can pick: This is the section, where you can pick and tag related blog articles that already exist or published on the website. This will help the readers to consume similar blog articles as well, in order to gather more information.

common.Promotions are available for promoting p: Promotions are available for promoting particular products or categories of products on the home page, by displaying them to the visitors. Such a display can be given a title, e.g., hot summer offer, Christmas mega sale, etc. The title is recommended to be appealing enough to attract and induce the customers to click and navigate to the particular page to purchase the items.
common.The Positions is in which order such as: The Positions is in which order such as first or second or third in the list of promotions. A particular promotions position can be defined here.
common.A slug is the part of a URL that identif: A slug is the part of a URL that identifies a particular widgets details on a website in an easy-to-read form. In other words, its the part of the URL that explains the widgets content.
common.A description can be provided for the pr: A description can be provided for the promotion with content
common.In this section, you can map a particula: In this section, you can map a particular promotion to a category or some products. You can choose either category or the list of products individually.
common.A meta title, also known as a title tag,: A meta title, also known as a title tag, refers to the text that is displayed on search engine result pages and browser tabs to indicate the topic of a webpage. The recommended characters for meta title is between 60 to 70 characters, with spacing.
common.A meta description is an HTML element th: A meta description is an HTML element that provides a brief summary of a web page. A pages meta description tag is displayed as part of the search snippet in a search engine results page (SERP) and is meant to give the user an idea of the content that exists within the page and how it relates to their search query. The recommended characters for meta title is between 160 to 170 characters, with spacing.
common.Meta Keywords are a specific type of met: Meta Keywords are a specific type of meta tag that appear in the HTML code of a Web page and help tell search engines what the topic of the page is. The recommended characters for meta title is between 250 characters, with spacing. And, make sure each keyword is separated with a comma. Also, the keywords can be a mix of both short tail keywords and long tail keywords (phrases with 2 to 3 words).
common.A page title is a name or an identificat: A page title is a name or an identification for a particular page. The page title has to be relevant to the content on the page. The title should be appropriate enough so that when a user reads title, they should be able to expect the type of content in the text body.

localization.Categories: Provide equivalent category names in various languages to ensure customers can easily find products in their preferred language

localization.FamilyNote: Organize related product specifications by mapping attribute groups to categories, which will then fall under a family, allowing for improved categorization and management of similar products with relevant specifications.
